016af4c0-29a3-402b-a360-f23df23db202	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	My Morning Routine	my-morning-routine	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc ─æ╞ín giß║ún vß╗ü th├│i quen buß╗òi s├íng cß╗ºa mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i.	\N	I wake up at 7 o'clock every morning. First, I get out of bed and stretch. Then, I go to the bathroom to wash my face and brush my teeth. It feels good to be clean.\n\nAfter that, I go to the kitchen. I make a simple breakfast. Usually, it is toast and an egg. I also drink a glass of milk. Breakfast gives me energy for the day.\n\nNext, I get dressed. I choose my clothes for the day. I like wearing comfortable clothes. Then, I pack my bag with my books and my lunch.\n\nFinally, I leave my house at 8 o'clock. I walk to school. I see my friends on the way. It is a nice way to start my day.	EASY	2	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-13 19:00:06.834	2026-07-13 19:00:06.834	100	A1
d1cf0a17-a186-4d15-b43e-2b9e93eb5f22	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	A Typical Day for Sarah	a-typical-day-for-sarah	T├¼m hiß╗âu vß╗ü mß╗Öt ng├áy b├¼nh th╞░ß╗¥ng cß╗ºa Sarah, tß╗½ khi thß╗⌐c dß║¡y ─æß║┐n khi ─æi ngß╗º.	\N	Sarah wakes up at 7:00 AM every morning. She likes to start her day with a glass of water and some light stretching. After that, she brushes her teeth and washes her face. Then, she gets dressed in comfortable clothes for the day. She usually eats a simple breakfast, like toast or cereal, with a cup of tea.\n\nAt 8:30 AM, Sarah leaves her house to go to work. She works in an office downtown. She takes the bus, which is usually crowded. During her commute, she likes to listen to music or read a book on her phone. Her workday starts at 9:00 AM and ends at 5:00 PM. She has a lunch break at noon.\n\nAfter work, Sarah often goes to the gym for an hour. She enjoys exercising and staying healthy. Sometimes, she meets her friends for coffee after the gym. If she doesn't go to the gym, she goes straight home. She likes to cook dinner for herself and relax.\n\nIn the evening, Sarah usually watches TV or reads a book. She goes to bed around 10:30 PM. Before sleeping, she makes sure to set her alarm for the next day. She believes that a good routine helps her have a productive and happy life.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:00:16.46	2026-07-14 19:00:16.46	150	A2
e451de2f-0caa-4569-af35-ff03e67c398d	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	A Typical Day for Sarah	a-typical-day-for-sarah-1	B├ái ─æß╗ìc m├┤ tß║ú mß╗Öt ng├áy b├¼nh th╞░ß╗¥ng cß╗ºa Sarah, mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i phß╗Ñ nß╗» trß║╗ sß╗æng ß╗ƒ th├ánh phß╗æ, vß╗¢i c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng h├áng ng├áy tß╗½ s├íng ─æß║┐n tß╗æi.	\N	Sarah wakes up early every morning, usually around 6:30 AM. The first thing she does is stretch and then make a cup of coffee. After her coffee, she checks her emails and plans her day. Breakfast is usually something quick like yogurt with fruit or toast. She likes to start her day feeling organized and energized.\n\nHer commute to work takes about thirty minutes by bus. Sarah works in an office downtown as a graphic designer. Her job involves creating visual concepts, using computer software to generate designs, and meeting with clients to discuss their needs. She enjoys her work because it allows her to be creative and solve problems.\n\nAfter work, Sarah often meets up with friends for dinner or goes to the gym. Sometimes, she prefers a quiet evening at home, reading a book or watching a movie. On weekends, she likes to explore new cafes, visit museums, or go for walks in the park. She believes in maintaining a good balance between work and personal life.\n\nBefore going to bed, Sarah usually tidies up her apartment and prepares her clothes for the next day. She aims to be in bed by 10:30 PM to ensure she gets enough sleep. A good night's rest is important for her to feel refreshed and ready for whatever the new day brings.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:00:28.051	2026-07-14 19:00:28.051	250	B1
ed31fe3d-aa1c-43a6-94b5-732e30c20e1d	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	A Day in the Life of a Remote Worker	a-day-in-the-life-of-a-remote-worker	B├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü mß╗Öt ng├áy l├ám viß╗çc tß╗½ xa ─æiß╗ân h├¼nh, kh├ím ph├í nhß╗»ng th├ích thß╗⌐c v├á lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa n├│, c┼⌐ng nh╞░ c├ích duy tr├¼ sß╗▒ c├ón bß║▒ng giß╗»a c├┤ng viß╗çc v├á cuß╗Öc sß╗æng.	\N	My alarm usually goes off at 7:00 AM, but working remotely means I don't have to rush out the door. I appreciate this flexibility, which allows me to start my day at a more relaxed pace. After a quick breakfast and a cup of coffee, I usually spend about 30 minutes reading the news or doing some light stretching. This routine helps me transition from personal time to work mode without the stress of a morning commute. It's a significant perk of my job, enabling a healthier work-life balance.\n\nBy 8:30 AM, I'm usually at my desk, ready to dive into my tasks. My work involves a lot of writing and project management, which requires intense focus. However, working from home comes with its own set of distractions. The temptation to do a quick chore or check social media can be strong. This is where self-discipline becomes crucial. I've learned to set strict boundaries, using productivity apps and taking short, scheduled breaks to avoid procrastination and maintain my output.\n\nOne of the biggest benefits of remote work is the ability to integrate personal appointments seamlessly into my schedule. I can easily fit in a doctor's visit or a quick grocery run during off-peak hours, which would be impossible with a traditional office job. This flexibility also means I can sometimes work from a different location, like a coffee shop, for a change of scenery, which often boosts my creativity and motivation. It truly transforms the concept of a 'workday'.\n\nAs the workday winds down, usually around 5:30 PM, I make sure to properly log off and mentally switch gears. I resist the urge to check emails after hours, as maintaining a clear boundary is essential for my well-being. My evenings are typically spent cooking dinner, going for a walk, or catching up with friends and family. Reading a book or watching a documentary helps me unwind completely before heading to bed. This structured approach ensures that the lines between work and personal life don't blur too much.	EASY	3	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:01:16.266	2026-07-14 19:01:16.266	305	B2
5762a025-870d-434e-8081-a3f377d17c39	7eb287c5-fba0-45a9-9cb9-18f366ed44ca	My School Day	my-school-day	B├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü mß╗Öt ng├áy hß╗ìc tß║¡p tß║íi tr╞░ß╗¥ng cß╗ºa mß╗Öt bß║ín nhß╗Å.	\N	Hello! My name is Lily. I am six years old. I go to primary school. School starts at 8 o'clock in the morning. I like my school very much.\n\nIn school, I learn many things. I learn English words and numbers in Math. My teacher is kind. Her name is Ms. Anna. She helps us learn and play.\n\nAt 12 o'clock, it is lunchtime. I eat my sandwich and fruit. I play with my friends, Tom and Mia, in the playground. We run and laugh together.\n\nSchool finishes at 3 o'clock in the afternoon. My mom picks me up. I go home and do my homework. Then I play with my toys. School is fun!	EASY	3	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:01:53.573	2026-07-14 19:01:53.573	105	A1
84adcebc-6cc9-47b5-830d-8dc5dc760b4d	7eb287c5-fba0-45a9-9cb9-18f366ed44ca	My School Day	my-school-day-1	Mß╗Öt ng├áy hß╗ìc tß║¡p tß║íi tr╞░ß╗¥ng cß╗ºa t├┤i.	\N	My school is a nice place. It has many classrooms and a big library. I go to school every Monday to Friday. I wake up early at 6:30 AM. Then, I eat breakfast with my family. After breakfast, I walk to school with my friends. It takes about 15 minutes.\n\nAt school, my first class is English. I like English very much. My teacher is very kind. After English, I have Math class. Math is a little difficult for me, but I try my best. We also have Science and History. I learn many new things every day.\n\nDuring the break, I often play games with my friends in the playground. Sometimes, we eat snacks together. The school cafeteria has good food. After the break, we go back to our classrooms for more lessons. My favorite subject is Art because I love drawing.\n\nWhen school finishes at 4:00 PM, I go home. I do my homework first. Then, I can play or watch TV. I think school is important for my future. It helps me learn and grow.	EASY	5	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:02:09.949	2026-07-14 19:02:09.949	150	A2
cd862298-8a0f-46c4-aabb-4eade486cd2d	7eb287c5-fba0-45a9-9cb9-18f366ed44ca	The Evolving Landscape of Modern Education	the-evolving-landscape-of-modern-education	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy kh├ím ph├í nhß╗»ng thay ─æß╗òi v├á xu h╞░ß╗¢ng ch├¡nh trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc hiß╗çn ─æß║íi, tß╗½ mß╗Ñc ti├¬u hß╗ìc tß║¡p ─æß║┐n vai tr├▓ cß╗ºa c├┤ng nghß╗ç v├á kß╗╣ n─âng mß╗üm.	\N	Education today is more than just memorizing facts; it's about preparing students for a rapidly changing world. Modern schooling aims to develop critical thinking, problem-solving skills, and creativity. It encourages students to ask questions, explore different ideas, and understand how to learn independently. This approach helps them become lifelong learners, ready to adapt to new challenges and opportunities.\n\nTechnology plays a significant role in contemporary education. Interactive whiteboards, tablets, and online learning platforms have become common tools in classrooms. These technologies can make lessons more engaging and accessible, offering students new ways to interact with information. For example, virtual field trips can take students to distant places, and educational apps can provide personalized learning experiences tailored to individual needs.\n\nBeyond academic subjects, schools also focus on developing 'soft skills' such as communication, teamwork, and leadership. Participating in extracurricular activities like sports, clubs, or volunteer work is crucial. These activities teach valuable life lessons, help students discover their interests, and build confidence. They also provide opportunities to apply classroom knowledge in practical, real-world situations.\n\nThe concept of education is evolving. Learning is no longer confined to school years; it's a continuous process throughout life. Many adults return to education to gain new qualifications or update their skills for career advancement. Online courses and professional development programs make it easier than ever to continue learning at any age. This lifelong learning approach ensures individuals remain relevant and adaptable in their professional and personal lives.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:02:52.444	2026-07-14 19:02:52.444	290	B1
06577697-7aa0-47fa-9d43-52ea80ce347f	7eb287c5-fba0-45a9-9cb9-18f366ed44ca	The Evolving Landscape of Higher Education	the-evolving-landscape-of-higher-education	Kh├ím ph├í nhß╗»ng thay ─æß╗òi v├á xu h╞░ß╗¢ng mß╗¢i trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc ─æß║íi hß╗ìc, tß╗½ ph╞░╞íng ph├íp giß║úng dß║íy ─æß║┐n vai tr├▓ cß╗ºa c├┤ng nghß╗ç.	\N	Higher education is undergoing a significant transformation, moving beyond traditional lecture halls and rigid curricula. Universities worldwide are increasingly embracing innovative pedagogical approaches, such as blended learning, project-based assignments, and flipped classrooms. These methods aim to foster critical thinking, problem-solving skills, and greater student engagement, preparing graduates for a dynamic job market that demands adaptability and lifelong learning. The focus is shifting from mere knowledge acquisition to the development of competencies and practical application of learned material.\n\nThe integration of technology has been a pivotal force in this evolution. Online learning platforms, virtual reality simulations, and artificial intelligence tools are not only expanding access to education but also personalizing the learning experience. Students can now access a wealth of resources anytime, anywhere, and learn at their own pace. This technological advancement also enables educators to track student progress more effectively and tailor their instruction to individual needs, creating a more inclusive and efficient educational environment.\n\nFurthermore, the concept of a university degree is broadening. Micro-credentials, bootcamps, and specialized online courses are gaining popularity as alternatives or supplements to traditional degrees. These shorter, more focused programs cater to specific industry needs and allow individuals to upskill or reskill quickly. This flexibility is crucial in a rapidly changing economy where career paths are often non-linear and continuous professional development is essential.\n\nHowever, challenges remain. Ensuring equitable access to these new educational models, maintaining academic integrity in online settings, and adequately training faculty to utilize new technologies are ongoing concerns. Universities must navigate these complexities to ensure that higher education remains relevant, accessible, and effective in equipping future generations with the knowledge and skills they need to thrive in the 21st century.	EASY	7	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:03:05.645	2026-07-14 19:03:05.645	350	B2
d6bc69ef-1b4a-4dfb-a4d2-7290900e954b	5c6a91f7-0a43-45c3-a5ed-258f4e07a632	Our Beautiful Planet	our-beautiful-planet	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc ─æ╞ín giß║ún vß╗ü m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng, gi├║p ng╞░ß╗¥i hß╗ìc ß╗ƒ tr├¼nh ─æß╗Ö A1 l├ám quen vß╗¢i c├íc tß╗½ vß╗▒ng c╞í bß║ún li├¬n quan ─æß║┐n thi├¬n nhi├¬n.	\N	The Earth is our home. It is a beautiful planet. We have trees, flowers, and rivers. The sky is blue and the sun is bright. We love our planet.	EASY	2	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:03:18.122	2026-07-14 19:03:18.122	100	A1
cac4d6ae-bb66-4c29-914d-d2e942056862	5c6a91f7-0a43-45c3-a5ed-258f4e07a632	Our Beautiful Planet	our-beautiful-planet-1	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc ─æ╞ín giß║ún vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc bß║úo vß╗ç m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng.	\N	Our planet Earth is very beautiful. It has green forests, blue oceans, and tall mountains. Many animals and plants live here. We need to take care of our Earth. It is our home.\n\nPollution is a big problem. It makes the air and water dirty. We can help by not throwing trash on the ground. We should put our trash in bins. Recycling is also important. It helps reduce waste.\n\nWe can save energy too. Turn off lights when you leave a room. Walk or ride a bike instead of driving a car for short distances. These small actions can make a big difference.\n\nLet's work together to keep our planet clean and healthy. A healthy environment is good for everyone. We want our children to enjoy a beautiful Earth.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:03:34.578	2026-07-14 19:03:34.578	150	A2
59e8da14-beed-45ea-bbbb-6565d0962f44	5c6a91f7-0a43-45c3-a5ed-258f4e07a632	Protecting Our Planet	protecting-our-planet	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc bß║úo vß╗ç m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng v├á nhß╗»ng h├ánh ─æß╗Öng ─æ╞ín giß║ún ch├║ng ta c├│ thß╗â l├ám.	\N	Our planet Earth is a beautiful place, but it is facing many environmental problems. Pollution from factories and cars makes the air and water dirty. Deforestation, cutting down too many trees, causes problems for animals and contributes to climate change. We need to take action to protect our environment for future generations.\n\nThere are many simple things we can do in our daily lives to help. Recycling is a great way to reduce waste. We can separate our trash into paper, plastic, and glass. Using less energy, like turning off lights when we leave a room, also helps. Walking or cycling instead of driving short distances is good for our health and the environment.\n\nAnother important action is to conserve water. We should fix leaky taps and avoid wasting water when brushing our teeth or washing dishes. Planting trees is also very beneficial. Trees clean the air, provide homes for wildlife, and make our surroundings more beautiful. Even small actions, when done by many people, can make a big difference.\n\nEducating ourselves and others about environmental issues is crucial. When we understand the problems, we are more likely to make positive changes. By working together and making conscious choices, we can help preserve the natural beauty of our planet and ensure a healthier future for everyone. Let's all do our part to protect our environment.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:03:47.425	2026-07-14 19:03:47.425	250	B1
0cb8833a-63e9-4b2f-b460-470af92b366d	5c6a91f7-0a43-45c3-a5ed-258f4e07a632	Our Planet's Delicate Balance	our-planet-s-delicate-balance	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc bß║úo vß╗ç m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng v├á nhß╗»ng h├ánh ─æß╗Öng ch├║ng ta c├│ thß╗â thß╗▒c hiß╗çn.	\N	The Earth's environment is a complex and interconnected system, where every element plays a crucial role in maintaining a delicate balance. From the vast oceans that regulate our climate to the microscopic organisms in the soil that support plant life, nature's intricate web sustains all living beings. However, human activities have increasingly disrupted this equilibrium, leading to significant environmental challenges that threaten the planet's health and our own future.\n\nOne of the most pressing issues is climate change, primarily driven by the emission of greenhouse gases from burning fossil fuels. This leads to rising global temperatures, melting ice caps, and more extreme weather events. Deforestation, pollution of air and water, and the loss of biodiversity are other critical concerns. These problems are not isolated; they often exacerbate one another, creating a domino effect that impacts ecosystems worldwide.\n\nAddressing these environmental threats requires a collective effort from individuals, communities, and governments. Simple actions, such as reducing waste, conserving energy, and choosing sustainable products, can make a significant difference when adopted on a large scale. Furthermore, supporting policies that promote renewable energy, protect natural habitats, and encourage responsible consumption is vital for long-term environmental sustainability.\n\nEducation and awareness are also key components in fostering a sense of responsibility towards our planet. By understanding the consequences of our actions and the importance of environmental conservation, we can inspire change and work together to preserve the Earth for future generations. It is our shared duty to protect and cherish the natural world that provides us with life and beauty.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:03:59.473	2026-07-14 19:03:59.473	280	B2
82f71c77-350e-4232-b338-2863d6428273	c050c74c-036a-432d-809f-8e5f23d9a9e8	My New Phone	my-new-phone	B├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü chiß║┐c ─æiß╗çn thoß║íi mß╗¢i cß╗ºa t├┤i, giß╗¢i thiß╗çu c├íc chß╗⌐c n─âng c╞í bß║ún.	\N	I have a new phone. It is black. I like my phone. It is small and light. I can put it in my pocket.\n\nMy phone has a screen. The screen is bright. I can see pictures on the screen. I can play games on my phone.\n\nI can talk to my friends on my phone. I can send messages too. My phone helps me stay in touch.\n\nI can also use my phone for music. I listen to songs when I walk. My new phone is very useful.	EASY	2	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:04:09.885	2026-07-14 19:04:09.885	100	A1
f6569cf2-3510-48e5-8506-6c00b7f8df55	c050c74c-036a-432d-809f-8e5f23d9a9e8	My New Smartphone	my-new-smartphone	B├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü chiß║┐c ─æiß╗çn thoß║íi th├┤ng minh mß╗¢i cß╗ºa t├┤i, giß╗¢i thiß╗çu c├íc chß╗⌐c n─âng c╞í bß║ún v├á lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa n├│.	\N	I have a new smartphone. It is black and has a big screen. I use it every day. It helps me a lot with my school work and talking to my friends.\n\nI can use the internet on my phone. I search for information for my homework. I also watch videos and listen to music. It is very fun.\n\nMy phone has a camera. I take pictures of my family and my cat. The pictures are very clear. I can also send these pictures to my friends.\n\nI like my new smartphone. It makes my life easier. I can learn new things and stay connected with people. It is a very useful device.	EASY	5	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:04:26.802	2026-07-14 19:04:26.802	150	A2
a9ab83b2-89ba-4541-a409-11c69fabbb60	c050c74c-036a-432d-809f-8e5f23d9a9e8	The Rise of Smartphones	the-rise-of-smartphones	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân v├á ß║únh h╞░ß╗ƒng cß╗ºa ─æiß╗çn thoß║íi th├┤ng minh trong cuß╗Öc sß╗æng hiß╗çn ─æß║íi.	\N	Smartphones have become an essential part of our daily lives. These small, portable devices allow us to communicate, access information, and entertain ourselves wherever we go. From making calls and sending messages to browsing the internet and using social media, smartphones offer a wide range of functionalities that have transformed how we interact with the world.\n\nOne of the most significant impacts of smartphones is on communication. They have made it easier than ever to stay connected with friends, family, and colleagues. Video calls, instant messaging apps, and social networking platforms allow us to share our lives and experiences in real-time, bridging geographical distances. This constant connectivity, however, also raises questions about privacy and the quality of our interactions.\n\nBeyond communication, smartphones are powerful tools for learning and productivity. With countless educational apps, e-books, and online resources, they provide access to knowledge on demand. Many people also use their smartphones for work, managing emails, scheduling appointments, and collaborating on projects. The ability to carry a computer in our pocket has undoubtedly boosted efficiency for many individuals and businesses.\n\nHowever, the widespread use of smartphones also presents challenges. Excessive screen time can lead to eye strain, sleep problems, and a decrease in physical activity. It's important to find a balance and ensure that technology serves us, rather than controls us. Setting limits on usage and being mindful of our digital habits are crucial steps towards a healthier relationship with our smartphones.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:04:38.635	2026-07-14 19:04:38.635	250	B1
d050607f-b1da-4125-9192-f85c0d0cd381	c050c74c-036a-432d-809f-8e5f23d9a9e8	The Rise of Artificial Intelligence	the-rise-of-artificial-intelligence	Kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân v├á t├íc ─æß╗Öng cß╗ºa Tr├¡ tuß╗ç Nh├ón tß║ío (AI) trong cuß╗Öc sß╗æng hiß╗çn ─æß║íi.	\N	Artificial Intelligence (AI) has rapidly evolved from a futuristic concept into a tangible force shaping our daily lives. Initially confined to academic research and science fiction, AI is now integrated into numerous applications, from virtual assistants on our smartphones to sophisticated algorithms powering recommendation systems on streaming platforms. This widespread adoption signifies a major technological shift, offering unprecedented convenience and efficiency.\n\nThe capabilities of AI are expanding at an astonishing pace. Machine learning, a subset of AI, allows systems to learn from data without explicit programming, leading to continuous improvement and adaptation. This enables AI to perform complex tasks such as image recognition, natural language processing, and even medical diagnosis with remarkable accuracy. As AI systems become more advanced, they are increasingly capable of assisting humans in various professional fields, augmenting our abilities and productivity.\n\nHowever, the proliferation of AI also raises significant ethical and societal questions. Concerns about job displacement due to automation, data privacy, and the potential for bias in AI algorithms are subjects of ongoing debate. Ensuring that AI development is guided by ethical principles and regulatory frameworks is crucial to harness its benefits while mitigating potential risks. The responsible implementation of AI requires careful consideration of its impact on individuals and society as a whole.\n\nLooking ahead, the future of AI promises further innovation and integration into even more aspects of our lives. From autonomous vehicles to personalized education and advanced scientific research, AI holds the potential to solve some of the world's most pressing challenges. Continued research, collaboration, and open discussion will be vital in navigating the path forward, ensuring that AI serves humanity's best interests and contributes to a more prosperous and equitable future.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:04:50.958	2026-07-14 19:04:50.958	350	B2
baed85c3-047a-4eac-9818-564a6f2ffc11	b7e03a7d-69c2-41e1-8f7a-3f7b21b1a2aa	The Sun and the Moon	the-sun-and-the-moon	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc ─æ╞ín giß║ún vß╗ü Mß║╖t Trß╗¥i v├á Mß║╖t Tr─âng, hai thi├¬n thß╗â quen thuß╗Öc tr├¬n bß║ºu trß╗¥i.	\N	The sun is big and hot. It is yellow. We see the sun in the day. The sun gives us light and warmth. It helps plants grow.\n\nThe moon is smaller than the sun. It is white or gray. We see the moon at night. The moon does not make its own light. It reflects light from the sun.\n\nSometimes, we see the full moon. It looks like a big circle. Sometimes, we see a small part of the moon. It looks like a smile.\n\nThe sun and the moon are important. They are in the sky. We can see them every day and night.	EASY	2	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:00.396	2026-07-14 19:05:00.396	85	A1
bc64004e-9d15-4540-b0b5-fd306757a407	b7e03a7d-69c2-41e1-8f7a-3f7b21b1a2aa	The Amazing Water Cycle	the-amazing-water-cycle	T├¼m hiß╗âu vß╗ü chu tr├¼nh n╞░ß╗¢c v├á tß║íi sao n├│ lß║íi quan trß╗ìng ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i sß╗▒ sß╗æng tr├¬n Tr├íi ─Éß║Ñt.	\N	Water is very important for all living things. We drink water, plants need water, and animals need water. But where does water come from? Most of the water on Earth is in oceans, rivers, and lakes. This water moves around in a cycle called the water cycle.\n\nThe water cycle has different steps. First, the sun heats the water in oceans and lakes. This warm water turns into a gas called water vapor. This is called evaporation. The water vapor goes up into the sky.\n\nNext, the water vapor in the sky cools down. It turns back into tiny water drops or ice crystals. These drops and crystals form clouds. This is called condensation. When the clouds get full of water, the water falls back to Earth as rain, snow, or hail. This is called precipitation.\n\nFinally, the water that falls on the ground goes back into rivers, lakes, and oceans. Some water goes deep into the ground. Then, the sun heats the water again, and the cycle starts over. The water cycle helps bring fresh water to all parts of the Earth.	EASY	5	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:10.858	2026-07-14 19:05:10.858	150	A2
b50903ce-9e98-4864-9ae2-e29389347e57	b7e03a7d-69c2-41e1-8f7a-3f7b21b1a2aa	The Amazing World of Bees	the-amazing-world-of-bees	T├¼m hiß╗âu vß╗ü vai tr├▓ quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa lo├ái ong trong hß╗ç sinh th├íi v├á cuß╗Öc sß╗æng cß╗ºa ch├║ng ta.	\N	Bees are small, flying insects that are incredibly important for our planet. They are famous for making honey, but their most crucial role is pollination. Pollination is the process where bees transfer pollen from one flower to another, which helps plants produce fruits and seeds. Without bees, many of the fruits, vegetables, and nuts we eat would not exist.\n\nThere are thousands of different species of bees around the world, not just the honeybees we often see. Some bees live alone, while others live in large colonies. Honeybees live in complex societies with a queen bee, worker bees, and drone bees. Each type of bee has a specific job to do to keep the colony running smoothly. The queen lays eggs, the worker bees collect food and build the hive, and the drones' main purpose is to mate with a queen.\n\nBees communicate with each other in fascinating ways. One famous method is the 'waggle dance'. When a worker bee finds a good source of nectar or pollen, it returns to the hive and performs this dance. The dance tells other bees the direction and distance to the food source. This allows the colony to efficiently gather resources needed for survival.\n\nUnfortunately, bee populations are facing serious threats. Pesticides, habitat loss, and climate change are making it harder for bees to survive. Protecting bees is vital for maintaining biodiversity and ensuring our food supply. We can help by planting bee-friendly flowers, avoiding harmful pesticides in our gardens, and supporting local beekeepers.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:23.4	2026-07-14 19:05:23.4	250	B1
668717a4-2fc6-4814-87ce-da26bdfa5366	b7e03a7d-69c2-41e1-8f7a-3f7b21b1a2aa	The Fascinating World of Bioluminescence	the-fascinating-world-of-bioluminescence	Kh├ím ph├í hiß╗çn t╞░ß╗úng ph├ít quang sinh hß╗ìc kß╗│ diß╗çu trong tß╗▒ nhi├¬n, tß╗½ s├óu d╞░ß╗¢i ─æß║íi d╞░╞íng ─æß║┐n nhß╗»ng c├ính rß╗½ng ─æ├¬m.	\N	Bioluminescence, the production and emission of light by a living organism, is a captivating natural phenomenon. It occurs widely in marine vertebrates and invertebrates, as well as in some fungi, microorganisms including some bioluminescent bacteria, and terrestrial arthropods such as fireflies. This 'living light' is not a result of heat, unlike incandescence, but is produced through a chemical reaction involving a light-emitting molecule called luciferin and an enzyme called luciferase. The specific chemicals and mechanisms can vary significantly between different species, leading to a diverse array of light colors and patterns.\n\nIn the deep ocean, where sunlight cannot penetrate, bioluminescence plays a crucial role in survival. Many deep-sea creatures use their light to attract prey, communicate with potential mates, or startle predators. For instance, anglerfish famously use a bioluminescent lure to draw unsuspecting smaller fish towards their mouths. Other organisms might use their light for camouflage, a technique known as counter-illumination, where they produce light on their undersides to match the faint light filtering down from the surface, making them less visible to predators lurking below.\n\nOn land, fireflies are perhaps the most well-known example of bioluminescence. Their flashing patterns are not just for show; they are a complex language used for courtship. Each species has a unique flash pattern, and males and females use these signals to find and identify each other. Some fungi also exhibit bioluminescence, often referred to as 'foxfire', which can create an eerie glow in damp forests. While the exact purpose for fungal bioluminescence is still debated, it's thought to attract insects that help disperse the fungal spores.\n\nStudying bioluminescence offers valuable insights into biochemistry and ecology. Scientists are exploring its potential applications in various fields, including medicine and environmental monitoring. For example, bioluminescent markers can be used to track biological processes within cells or to detect pollutants in water. The efficiency and specificity of the light-producing reaction make it an attractive tool for technological innovation, promising further discoveries and applications in the future.	EASY	7	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:37.884	2026-07-14 19:05:37.884	350	B2
5e2e4578-2b19-4ddf-89e3-db54bb68b68a	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	My Family's Traditions	my-family-s-traditions	T├¼m hiß╗âu vß╗ü nhß╗»ng truyß╗ün thß╗æng gia ─æ├¼nh ─æ╞ín giß║ún v├á ├╜ ngh─⌐a cß╗ºa ch├║ng.	\N	My family has special traditions. Every Sunday, we eat dinner together. We talk about our week. It is a happy time for us.\n\nOn my birthday, my family sings a song for me. They give me a cake. I like my birthday very much.\n\nIn December, we decorate our house. We put up lights and a tree. It looks very beautiful.\n\nThese traditions are important. They make our family strong and happy. We love our traditions.	EASY	3	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:48.247	2026-07-14 19:05:48.247	120	A1
51fb0089-085d-4a96-8aa7-f29c91d18bda	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	Festivals Around the World	festivals-around-the-world	T├¼m hiß╗âu vß╗ü mß╗Öt sß╗æ lß╗à hß╗Öi th├║ vß╗ï tr├¬n thß║┐ giß╗¢i.	\N	Festivals are special times for people to celebrate. Many countries have unique festivals. These celebrations often involve music, dancing, and special food. People get together with family and friends to have fun.\n\nIn Japan, there is the Cherry Blossom Festival. People go to parks to see the beautiful pink flowers. They have picnics under the trees. It is a very peaceful and pretty time.\n\nIn India, people celebrate Holi, the Festival of Colors. They throw colored powder and water at each other. It is a very joyful and energetic festival. Everyone laughs and plays together.\n\nIn Brazil, the Carnival is a big party. People wear colorful costumes and dance in the streets. There is loud music and parades. It is a very exciting celebration.	EASY	5	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:05:59.775	2026-07-14 19:05:59.775	150	A2
87ae75fc-d76c-4a36-a8ab-d0309e5ea045	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	Festivals Around the World	festivals-around-the-world-1	Kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ─æa dß║íng cß╗ºa c├íc lß╗à hß╗Öi tr├¬n khß║»p thß║┐ giß╗¢i, tß╗½ nhß╗»ng lß╗à kß╗╖ niß╗çm truyß╗ün thß╗æng ─æß║┐n nhß╗»ng sß╗▒ kiß╗çn hiß╗çn ─æß║íi.	\N	Festivals are a wonderful way to experience different cultures. They are special events that people celebrate for many reasons, such as religious holidays, historical events, or the changing seasons. Many festivals involve music, dancing, special food, and colorful decorations. They bring communities together and create a sense of shared identity and joy.\n\nOne famous festival is Diwali, the Festival of Lights, celebrated by Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and some Buddhists. It symbolizes the victory of light over darkness and good over evil. People light oil lamps called diyas, decorate their homes, and share sweets with family and friends. Fireworks are also a common sight during Diwali celebrations.\n\nAnother vibrant festival is Carnival, particularly famous in Brazil and other parts of Latin America. It's a time of parades, elaborate costumes, samba music, and dancing. People celebrate with great energy before the period of Lent. Carnival is a fantastic display of creativity and community spirit.\n\nIn many parts of Asia, the Lunar New Year is a significant celebration. It marks the beginning of the new year according to the lunisolar calendar. Families gather for reunion dinners, give red envelopes with money as gifts, and clean their homes to welcome good fortune. Lion dances and dragon dances are often performed to scare away evil spirits and bring good luck.	EASY	5	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:06:11.192	2026-07-14 19:06:11.192	250	B1
3a0929de-1aa8-4ea3-9ac4-8a56f73c7870	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	The Evolution of Festivals: More Than Just Celebration	the-evolution-of-festivals-more-than-just-celebration	Kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân cß╗ºa c├íc lß╗à hß╗Öi, tß╗½ nguß╗ôn gß╗æc cß╗ò x╞░a ─æß║┐n vai tr├▓ hiß╗çn ─æß║íi trong viß╗çc gß║»n kß║┐t cß╗Öng ─æß╗ông v├á bß║úo tß╗ôn v─ân h├│a.	\N	Festivals, in their myriad forms, have been a cornerstone of human civilization for millennia. Originally, many festivals were deeply intertwined with agricultural cycles, marking the seasons of planting and harvesting. These events served a crucial purpose: to appease deities, ensure a bountiful yield, and foster a sense of community among people facing the shared challenges of survival. Rituals, feasting, and storytelling were common elements, reinforcing social bonds and passing down vital knowledge from one generation to the next.\n\nAs societies evolved, so did the nature and purpose of festivals. While agricultural roots remained significant for some, others emerged to commemorate historical events, honor religious figures, or celebrate significant life transitions like births and marriages. The Roman Saturnalia, for instance, evolved from a harvest festival into a period of revelry and role reversal, demonstrating how cultural practices adapt to changing social structures and beliefs. This adaptability highlights festivals' dynamic nature, reflecting the values and priorities of the societies that observe them.\n\nIn the modern era, festivals continue to play a vital role, though their functions have expanded. Beyond their traditional celebratory and spiritual aspects, festivals have become powerful tools for cultural preservation and economic development. They offer a platform for artists, musicians, and craftspeople to showcase their talents, attracting tourists and boosting local economies. Furthermore, by bringing people together to share experiences and traditions, festivals reinforce cultural identity and promote understanding between diverse groups.\n\nThe future of festivals likely involves a blend of tradition and innovation. While many will strive to maintain their historical authenticity, others may embrace new technologies and themes to remain relevant to contemporary audiences. The enduring appeal of festivals lies in their ability to connect us to our past, celebrate the present, and build a shared future. They remind us of our collective humanity and the importance of shared experiences in a rapidly changing world.	EASY	5	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-14 19:06:25.828	2026-07-14 19:06:25.828	350	B2
d024a0a1-9823-4960-8a58-614bb52eb880	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	A Typical Day	a-typical-day	Mß╗Öt ng├áy ─æiß╗ân h├¼nh cß╗ºa mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i trß║╗ tuß╗òi, bao gß╗ôm c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng h├áng ng├áy tß╗½ s├íng ─æß║┐n tß╗æi.	\N	My name is Sarah, and I want to tell you about my typical day. I wake up at 7:00 AM every morning. First, I brush my teeth and wash my face. Then, I eat breakfast. Usually, I have cereal or toast with milk. After breakfast, I get dressed and prepare to go to work.\n\nI work in an office from 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM. My job is interesting. I talk to many people and help them with their problems. I usually eat lunch at my desk around 1:00 PM. Sometimes, my colleagues and I go to a small cafe near the office for lunch.\n\nAfter work, I like to relax. Sometimes I go to the gym to exercise. Other times, I meet my friends for coffee. In the evening, I usually cook dinner at home. I enjoy eating healthy food like vegetables and chicken. After dinner, I watch TV or read a book before going to bed.\n\nI go to bed around 10:30 PM. Before sleeping, I always read a few pages of a book. This helps me relax and sleep well. My days are usually busy, but I enjoy them. I like having a routine because it makes me feel organized and happy.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:00:45.014	2026-07-16 19:00:45.014	150	A2
2e515816-36bc-42c2-b63d-dac31e9deb52	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	A Typical Weekday	a-typical-weekday	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy m├┤ tß║ú mß╗Öt ng├áy l├ám viß╗çc ─æiß╗ân h├¼nh cß╗ºa mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i, tß╗½ buß╗òi s├íng thß╗⌐c dß║¡y ─æß║┐n tß╗æi tr╞░ß╗¢c khi ─æi ngß╗º, gi├║p bß║ín l├ám quen vß╗¢i c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng v├á tß╗½ vß╗▒ng th├┤ng dß╗Ñng trong cuß╗Öc sß╗æng h├áng ng├áy.	\N	Every morning, my alarm clock usually rings at 6:30 AM. I'm not a morning person, so it's always a struggle to get out of bed. After a quick shower, I head to the kitchen to make breakfast. My usual choice is toast with jam and a cup of coffee. I like to check the news on my phone while I eat, keeping myself informed about what's happening in the world.\n\nThen, I get ready for work. My office is about 30 minutes away by bus, so I usually leave home around 7:45 AM. The commute can be quite busy, especially during peak hours, but I often listen to podcasts to pass the time. At work, my main responsibilities involve managing projects and communicating with clients. It can be challenging, but I enjoy problem-solving.\n\nAfter work, I often go to the gym for an hour or so. Staying active is important to me, and it helps me relax after a long day. Sometimes, I meet up with friends for dinner or a movie. If I stay home, I might cook a simple meal, read a book, or watch a TV series. I try to avoid too much screen time before bed.\n\nBefore going to sleep, I like to prepare my clothes for the next day and make a quick to-do list. This helps me feel organized and reduces morning stress. I usually go to bed around 10:30 PM, aiming for at least seven hours of sleep. A good night's rest is essential for me to feel energized and ready to face another day.	MEDIUM	3	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:01:45.789	2026-07-16 19:01:45.789	185	B1
f58ee8ea-d5d7-469f-b0e1-02675f46d6e3	06862269-de15-4c30-ba5c-5f0ee1f4bc54	The Rhythm of My Day	the-rhythm-of-my-day	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy m├┤ tß║ú mß╗Öt ng├áy ─æiß╗ân h├¼nh cß╗ºa mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i trß║╗ sß╗æng ß╗ƒ th├ánh phß╗æ, tß╗½ c├┤ng viß╗çc ─æß║┐n c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng giß║úi tr├¡ v├á t╞░╞íng t├íc x├ú hß╗Öi, ph├╣ hß╗úp vß╗¢i tr├¼nh ─æß╗Ö B2.	\N	My weekdays typically kick off at 6:30 AM, a time I've grown accustomed to. After a quick shower and a light breakfast, I meticulously plan my outfit for the day, ensuring I look presentable for my office job. The morning commute is often a test of patience; navigating the city's notorious traffic or squeezing onto a packed subway train is part of the daily hustle and bustle. By 8:30 AM, I'm usually at my desk, ready to dive into emails and prepare for the day's tasks.\n\nThe core of my workday revolves around project management. I spend a significant portion of my time in meetings, where we collaborate with team members to brainstorm solutions and strategize for upcoming deadlines. Lunch is a brief but welcome respite, often spent grabbing a quick bite with colleagues or, on quieter days, catching up on personal reading. The afternoon typically involves focused work, tackling complex problems, and ensuring our projects stay on track.\n\nAs the clock approaches 5:00 PM, a sense of anticipation builds. After work, I usually head straight to the gym for a workout, which is my preferred way to unwind and de-stress. On other evenings, I might pursue a hobby like photography or spend time cooking a new recipe. These activities are crucial for maintaining a healthy work-life balance and help me feel rejuvenated, ready to tackle whatever comes next.\n\nEvenings are a mix of social interaction and personal reflection. Sometimes I meet friends for dinner or a casual chat, catching up on our lives. Other times, it's a quiet evening at home, perhaps watching a documentary or reading a novel. Before bed, I often take a few moments to reflect on the day, practicing gratitude for the small successes and planning for the challenges of tomorrow. This routine, while seemingly repetitive, provides a comforting structure to my daily life.	EASY	10	5	20	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:02:35.628	2026-07-16 19:02:35.628	320	B2
98fa0956-c348-48de-a498-e42c83f2382d	7eb287c5-fba0-45a9-9cb9-18f366ed44ca	The Evolution of Learning: Beyond Traditional Classrooms	the-evolution-of-learning-beyond-traditional-classrooms	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy kh├ím ph├í nhß╗»ng thay ─æß╗òi trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc hiß╗çn ─æß║íi, tß╗½ lß╗¢p hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng ─æß║┐n c├íc ph╞░╞íng ph├íp hß╗ìc tß║¡p mß╗¢i v├á vai tr├▓ cß╗ºa c├┤ng nghß╗ç.	\N	For many years, education primarily took place in traditional classrooms. Students would sit at desks, listen to a teacher, and learn from textbooks. This model has been effective for generations, providing a structured environment for learning. However, in today's fast-changing world, there's a growing need for education to adapt and offer more diverse ways of learning.\n\nOne significant shift is the rise of online learning. Platforms and courses available on the internet have made education more accessible than ever before. Students can now learn from anywhere, at any time, fitting their studies around other commitments. This flexibility is especially beneficial for adults returning to education or those living in remote areas.\n\nBeyond online platforms, modern education also emphasizes different teaching methods. Project-based learning, for example, encourages students to work together on real-world problems. This approach helps develop important skills like critical thinking, problem-solving, and collaboration. Instead of just memorizing facts, students learn to apply their knowledge creatively.\n\nTechnology plays a crucial role in these changes. From interactive whiteboards to educational apps and virtual reality, technology offers personalized learning experiences. It allows teachers to tailor lessons to individual student needs and provides access to a vast amount of information. The future of education will likely see even more integration of technology, making learning more engaging and effective for everyone.	EASY	8	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:04:13.731	2026-07-16 19:04:13.731	275	B1
1ce11edb-2343-4cd5-b315-12baa1dfb387	5c6a91f7-0a43-45c3-a5ed-258f4e07a632	The Urgent Need for Environmental Conservation	the-urgent-need-for-environmental-conservation	Mß╗Öt b├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc bß║úo vß╗ç m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng v├á nhß╗»ng h├ánh ─æß╗Öng ch├║ng ta c├│ thß╗â thß╗▒c hiß╗çn.	\N	Our planet is facing unprecedented environmental challenges. Climate change, pollution, and biodiversity loss are no longer distant threats but present realities impacting ecosystems and human societies worldwide. The consequences are far-reaching, from extreme weather events and rising sea levels to resource scarcity and health issues. Recognizing the severity of these problems is the first step towards finding sustainable solutions and ensuring a healthy planet for future generations.\n\nOne of the most significant contributors to environmental degradation is human activity. Industrial processes, deforestation, and unsustainable agricultural practices have led to widespread pollution of air, water, and soil. The excessive use of fossil fuels for energy production releases greenhouse gases, accelerating global warming. Furthermore, the accumulation of plastic waste in oceans and landfills poses a grave threat to wildlife and marine ecosystems, taking hundreds of years to decompose.\n\nFortunately, there are numerous ways individuals and communities can contribute to environmental conservation. Simple actions like reducing, reusing, and recycling waste, conserving water and energy, and choosing sustainable transportation methods can make a substantial difference. Supporting eco-friendly businesses, advocating for stronger environmental policies, and participating in local clean-up initiatives are also crucial steps. Education plays a vital role in raising awareness and fostering a sense of responsibility towards the environment.\n\nAddressing environmental issues requires a collective effort. Governments, corporations, and individuals must work together to implement effective conservation strategies. Investing in renewable energy sources, promoting sustainable land management, and protecting natural habitats are essential. By embracing a more sustainable lifestyle and actively participating in conservation efforts, we can mitigate the damage already done and work towards a healthier, more resilient planet for all.	EASY	5	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:05:49.444	2026-07-16 19:05:49.444	350	B2
9d317a1e-236e-4230-af3e-783b5e0b4daf	c050c74c-036a-432d-809f-8e5f23d9a9e8	The Rise of Smart Devices	the-rise-of-smart-devices	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân cß╗ºa c├íc thiß║┐t bß╗ï th├┤ng minh v├á ß║únh h╞░ß╗ƒng cß╗ºa ch├║ng ─æß║┐n cuß╗Öc sß╗æng h├áng ng├áy.	\N	Smart devices have become a common part of our lives. From smartphones in our pockets to smart speakers in our homes, these gadgets make many tasks easier. They can control lights, play music, and even help us order groceries with just a voice command. This technology connects us to information and entertainment like never before.\n\nOne of the most popular smart devices is the smartphone. It's not just for making calls anymore. We use it for browsing the internet, taking photos, navigating with GPS, and managing our schedules. Many apps are designed to help us learn new things, stay healthy, or connect with friends and family all over the world.\n\nSmart home technology is also growing rapidly. Devices like smart thermostats can learn our preferences and adjust the temperature automatically, saving energy. Smart security cameras allow us to monitor our homes from anywhere using our phones. These innovations aim to make our homes more comfortable, secure, and efficient.\n\nWhile smart devices offer many benefits, it's also important to be aware of potential downsides. We need to think about privacy and security when using these connected gadgets. However, as technology continues to advance, smart devices are likely to become even more integrated into our daily routines, offering new possibilities and conveniences.	EASY	5	5	15	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:06:22.231	2026-07-16 19:06:22.231	250	B1
99a7d434-23e9-4c30-a30a-19080c384861	b7e03a7d-69c2-41e1-8f7a-3f7b21b1a2aa	The Dawn of Artificial Intelligence: Shaping Our Future	the-dawn-of-artificial-intelligence-shaping-our-future	B├ái ─æß╗ìc n├áy kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân nhanh ch├│ng cß╗ºa tr├¡ tuß╗ç nh├ón tß║ío (AI) v├á nhß╗»ng t├íc ─æß╗Öng s├óu rß╗Öng cß╗ºa n├│ ─æß║┐n x├ú hß╗Öi v├á cuß╗Öc sß╗æng h├áng ng├áy cß╗ºa ch├║ng ta.	\N	Artificial Intelligence (AI) represents a profound paradigm shift in technology, rapidly transforming how we interact with the world. From complex algorithms to sophisticated machine learning models, AI is no longer a futuristic concept but a ubiquitous presence in our daily lives. Its evolution has been fueled by vast amounts of data and increasing computational power, enabling machines to perform tasks that once required human intellect.\n\nThe applications of AI are incredibly diverse and continue to expand. In healthcare, AI assists in diagnosing diseases more accurately and developing personalized treatment plans. Autonomous vehicles, powered by AI, promise safer and more efficient transportation. Educational platforms leverage AI to offer adaptive learning experiences, tailoring content to individual student needs. Even in entertainment and customer service, AI-driven systems augment human capabilities, providing instant support and personalized recommendations.\n\nHowever, the rapid advancement of AI also presents several ethical considerations and challenges. Concerns about job displacement, as AI automates routine tasks, require careful societal planning and reskilling initiatives. Privacy issues arise from the extensive data collection necessary for AI systems to function. Furthermore, ensuring AI systems are fair and unbiased, avoiding the perpetuation of existing societal prejudices, is a critical area of ongoing research and development.\n\nAs AI continues to evolve, a balanced approach is crucial. Harnessing its potential to solve global challenges, from climate change to disease eradication, while simultaneously mitigating its risks, is paramount. This requires collaboration among technologists, policymakers, and the public to establish robust regulatory frameworks and foster responsible innovation. Ultimately, the future of AI lies in our collective ability to guide its development towards a more equitable and prosperous world.	EASY	2	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:08:15.235	2026-07-16 19:08:15.235	285	B2
191a0b2d-d435-4764-8092-febc11a1cf85	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	My Favorite Holiday	my-favorite-holiday	B├ái ─æß╗ìc vß╗ü kß╗│ nghß╗ë y├¬u th├¡ch cß╗ºa mß╗Öt bß║ín nhß╗Å, giß╗¢i thiß╗çu c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng v├á cß║úm x├║c.	\N	My favorite holiday is summer. I love summer because the sun is warm. I can play outside with my friends. We go to the park and play games. It is very fun.\n\nIn summer, my family often goes to the beach. I like swimming in the sea. The water is blue and cool. I build sandcastles with my dad. My mom likes to read a book on the sand.\n\nWe eat ice cream at the beach. My favorite flavor is strawberry. It is sweet and cold. After swimming, we eat lunch. We eat sandwiches and drink juice.\n\nSummer is a happy time for me. I like the long days and the warm weather. I always look forward to summer vacation. It is the best time of the year.	EASY	2	5	10	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:08:26.013	2026-07-16 19:08:26.013	100	A1
98b775af-801b-46b2-bb7a-467c3b7bbd77	30b1f6aa-87bb-4321-b738-8691c187d385	The Evolution of Festivals	the-evolution-of-festivals	Kh├ím ph├í sß╗▒ ph├ít triß╗ân v├á ├╜ ngh─⌐a cß╗ºa c├íc lß╗à hß╗Öi truyß╗ün thß╗æng trong x├ú hß╗Öi hiß╗çn ─æß║íi.	\N	Festivals have always been an integral part of human societies, serving as vital occasions for celebration, remembrance, and community bonding. Historically, many festivals were deeply rooted in agricultural cycles, religious beliefs, or significant historical events. They provided a structured way for people to mark the passage of time, express gratitude, and reinforce social cohesion. From ancient harvest celebrations to solemn remembrance days, these events played a crucial role in shaping cultural identity and passing down traditions through generations.\n\nIn the modern era, the nature and purpose of festivals have undergone significant transformations. While many traditional festivals continue to be celebrated, often with adaptations to suit contemporary life, new types of festivals have emerged. These include music festivals, film festivals, and food festivals, which often cater to specific interests and attract diverse audiences. The rise of globalization and digital communication has also influenced festivals, allowing for wider participation and the sharing of cultural practices across borders, though sometimes leading to concerns about commercialization and cultural appropriation.\n\nThe social impact of festivals remains profound. They offer a unique opportunity for individuals to step away from their daily routines, connect with others, and experience a sense of collective joy or reflection. Festivals can foster a sense of belonging and shared identity, strengthening community ties. Furthermore, they often contribute to local economies through tourism and related activities. The planning and execution of large-scale festivals also require significant collaboration, promoting teamwork and organizational skills within communities.\n\nLooking ahead, the future of festivals likely involves a blend of tradition and innovation. As societies evolve, so too will the ways in which people choose to celebrate. There is a growing emphasis on sustainability and inclusivity in festival design, reflecting broader societal values. While the forms may change, the fundamental human need for shared experiences, cultural expression, and communal celebration is likely to ensure that festivals, in one form or another, will continue to thrive.	EASY	8	5	25	t	0	0	2026-07-16 19:09:10.025	2026-07-16 19:09:10.025	350	B2
