de5aa4a6-8c31-41c5-89fc-c0ff7266f6dd	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	Is it better to travel alone or with others?	travel-opinion-solo-vs-group-travel	Nhiß╗üu ng╞░ß╗¥i th├¡ch ─æi du lß╗ïch mß╗Öt m├¼nh ─æß╗â c├│ tß╗▒ do v├á trß║úi nghiß╗çm ri├¬ng. Trong khi ─æ├│, nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi th├¡ch ─æi c├╣ng bß║ín b├¿ hoß║╖c gia ─æ├¼nh ─æß╗â c├│ sß╗▒ ─æß╗ông h├ánh v├á chia sß║╗ trß║úi nghiß╗çm. Bß║ín ngh─⌐ sao? Theo bß║ín, c├ích n├áo tß╗æt h╞ín v├á tß║íi sao?	Express your opinion on whether traveling alone or with a group is more enjoyable and why.	80	150	B1	OPINION	1	t	2026-07-14 19:03:49.997	2026-07-14 19:03:49.997	20	\N	0	I think traveling with a group is much better than going alone. When you travel with friends or family, you can share all the amazing moments with them. You can talk about the beautiful sights you see and laugh about funny things that happen. Also, it can be safer to travel with others, especially in new places. You can split costs for accommodation and food, which often saves money. While traveling alone offers more freedom, I believe the joy of shared experiences and the support from your companions make group travel more memorable and fun. It helps create stronger bonds and lasting memories together.
574a4ccc-2c13-42cd-9442-630052054372	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	Exploring Local Culture or Visiting Famous Landmarks?	travel-opinion-culture-vs-landmarks	Khi ─æi du lß╗ïch, mß╗Öt sß╗æ ng╞░ß╗¥i muß╗æn ─æß║»m m├¼nh v├áo v─ân h├│a ─æß╗ïa ph╞░╞íng, gß║╖p gß╗í ng╞░ß╗¥i d├ón v├á thß╗¡ m├│n ─ân truyß╗ün thß╗æng. Nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi th├¡ch ─æß║┐n th─âm nhß╗»ng danh lam thß║»ng cß║únh nß╗òi tiß║┐ng v├á c├íc ─æiß╗âm du lß╗ïch lß╗¢n. Bß║ín th├¡ch c├ích n├áo h╞ín v├á tß║íi sao?	Share your view on whether it's more important to experience local culture or visit popular tourist attractions when traveling.	80	150	B1	OPINION	2	t	2026-07-14 19:03:50.008	2026-07-14 19:03:50.008	20	\N	0	For me, exploring local culture is much more important than just visiting famous landmarks. While big attractions like museums or historical sites are nice, they sometimes feel very touristy. When I travel, I want to understand the real life of the place. This means trying local food from small markets, talking to local people, and seeing how they live their daily lives. It makes the trip feel more authentic and special. You learn so much more about the world when you step outside the main tourist areas. Famous landmarks can be seen in pictures, but experiencing a culture gives you unique memories that stay with you forever.
a9401d6a-30f3-471b-9ef9-13999c6bab97	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	Relaxing Beach Holidays or Exciting Adventure Trips?	travel-opinion-beach-vs-adventure	Bß║ín th├¡ch ─æi nghß╗ë d╞░ß╗íng th╞░ gi├ún tr├¬n b├úi biß╗ân hay nhß╗»ng chuyß║┐n ─æi phi├¬u l╞░u mß║ío hiß╗âm nh╞░ leo n├║i hoß║╖c kh├ím ph├í rß╗½ng rß║¡m h╞ín? H├úy giß║úi th├¡ch l├╜ do tß║íi sao bß║ín chß╗ìn kiß╗âu du lß╗ïch ─æ├│.	Discuss your preference for either relaxing beach holidays or more adventurous trips, explaining your reasons.	80	150	B1	OPINION	3	t	2026-07-14 19:03:50.017	2026-07-14 19:03:50.017	20	\N	0	I definitely prefer exciting adventure trips over relaxing beach holidays. While lying on a beach sounds nice for a day or two, I get bored very quickly. I love the thrill of trying new things and challenging myself. For example, hiking in mountains, exploring a new city on foot, or even trying a new sport gives me a sense of accomplishment and discovery. Adventure trips create unforgettable stories and push me out of my comfort zone. ItΓÇÖs a chance to learn new skills and see amazing natural beauty. A beach holiday might be relaxing, but an adventure trip feels like a real experience that makes me feel alive.
dd1a7df3-a225-4da8-a07d-68779317185d	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	To Plan or Not to Plan? The Best Way to Travel	travel-opinion-planning-vs-spontaneous	Mß╗Öt sß╗æ ng╞░ß╗¥i th├¡ch l├¬n kß║┐ hoß║ích chi tiß║┐t cho mß╗ìi thß╗⌐ tr╞░ß╗¢c khi ─æi du lß╗ïch, tß╗½ kh├ích sß║ín ─æß║┐n c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng. Nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi th├¡ch ─æi du lß╗ïch tß╗▒ ph├ít, kh├┤ng c├│ kß║┐ hoß║ích cß╗æ ─æß╗ïnh. Bß║ín ngh─⌐ c├ích n├áo tß╗æt h╞ín v├á tß║íi sao?	Give your opinion on whether extensive planning or spontaneous travel is better for a trip.	80	150	B1	OPINION	4	t	2026-07-14 19:03:50.028	2026-07-14 19:03:50.028	20	\N	0	I believe that a balance between planning and spontaneity is the best way to travel, but if I had to choose, I would lean towards more planning. Having a basic plan for accommodation and transport can save a lot of stress and money. You don't want to arrive in a new city without a place to sleep or a way to get around. However, it's also important to leave some room for spontaneity. This allows you to discover hidden gems or change your plans if you hear about something interesting. Too much planning can make a trip feel like work, but no planning at all can lead to problems. A well-structured trip with flexible days is ideal.
