c0a4b2ef-9463-49bb-86d3-9f72d2256431	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	T├íc ─æß╗Öng ti├¬u cß╗▒c cß╗ºa du lß╗ïch ─æß║íi ch├║ng	travel-ielts-task2-negative-impacts-of-tourism	While tourism brings many advantages, it can also cause problems for local communities and the environment. What are the main negative impacts of mass tourism, and what measures can be taken to tackle these problems?	Du lß╗ïch mang lß║íi nhiß╗üu lß╗úi ├¡ch, nh╞░ng n├│ c┼⌐ng c├│ thß╗â g├óy ra vß║Ñn ─æß╗ü. H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n vß╗ü nhß╗»ng t├íc ─æß╗Öng ti├¬u cß╗▒c cß╗ºa du lß╗ïch ─æß║íi ch├║ng v├á c├ích giß║úi quyß║┐t ch├║ng.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	2	t	2026-07-14 19:04:44.346	2026-07-14 19:04:44.346	20	\N	0	Tourism can indeed have negative effects. One major problem is environmental damage. Many popular tourist spots suffer from pollution from litter and increased traffic. For instance, some beaches become dirty due to many visitors. Another issue is the impact on local culture. Sometimes, local traditions change to fit tourists' demands, losing their original meaning. To address these, governments should promote eco-tourism, encouraging visitors to respect nature. Also, limits could be set on the number of tourists in sensitive areas. Furthermore, educating tourists about local customs can help reduce cultural disrespect. These steps can make tourism more sustainable.
f1b46c72-26ed-4899-8019-1d6efae85a6a	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	Du lß╗ïch trong n╞░ß╗¢c hay quß╗æc tß║┐?	travel-ielts-task2-local-vs-international-travel	Some people prefer to travel within their own country, while others enjoy exploring different countries abroad. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of both types of travel and state which one you prefer.	Mß╗Öt sß╗æ ng╞░ß╗¥i th├¡ch ─æi du lß╗ïch trong n╞░ß╗¢c, trong khi nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi th├¡ch kh├ím ph├í c├íc quß╗æc gia kh├íc. Bß║ín ngh─⌐ loß║íi h├¼nh du lß╗ïch n├áo tß╗æt h╞ín v├á tß║íi sao?	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	3	t	2026-07-14 19:04:44.352	2026-07-14 19:04:44.352	20	\N	0	Both local and international travel have their own benefits. Traveling within one's own country is often cheaper and easier because there are no visa issues or long flights. It also allows people to learn more about their own nation's history and diverse regions. For example, visiting different provinces can show you unique local customs. On the other hand, international travel offers a chance to experience entirely new cultures, languages, and foods, which can be very enriching. It broadens your worldview significantly. While it can be more expensive and require more planning, the cultural immersion is often deeper. Personally, I prefer international travel because I love discovering totally new places and meeting people from different backgrounds, even if it costs more.
b43375db-ab67-44c3-be37-b5221ff96fd6	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	Tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc l├¬n kß║┐ hoß║ích cho chuyß║┐n ─æi	travel-ielts-task2-importance-of-trip-planning	Some people believe it is essential to plan every detail of a trip carefully before traveling, while others prefer to be spontaneous and make decisions on the go. Discuss both views and give your own opinion.	Viß╗çc l├¬n kß║┐ hoß║ích kß╗╣ l╞░ß╗íng cho mß╗Öt chuyß║┐n ─æi c├│ quan trß╗ìng kh├┤ng? H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n l├╜ do tß║íi sao mß╗ìi ng╞░ß╗¥i n├¬n hoß║╖c kh├┤ng n├¬n l├¬n kß║┐ hoß║ích tr╞░ß╗¢c khi ─æi du lß╗ïch.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	4	t	2026-07-14 19:04:44.356	2026-07-14 19:04:44.356	20	\N	0	Planning a trip has both advantages and disadvantages. For those who plan carefully, it helps to save money and time. You can book flights and hotels in advance, which is often cheaper. Also, having an itinerary means you won't miss important sights. For instance, knowing opening hours for museums is helpful. However, some people prefer spontaneous travel. This allows for more flexibility and unexpected adventures. They might discover hidden gems not listed in guidebooks. This can also lead to unique experiences. In my opinion, a balance is best. It's good to have a general plan for flights and accommodation, but leave some days open for spontaneous activities. This way, you get the benefits of both planning and flexibility.
d4651920-4e90-4e12-9406-568085557752	7b6ff71d-8b60-43c5-84dc-ecf8b5997977	C├┤ng nghß╗ç thay ─æß╗òi c├ích ch├║ng ta du lß╗ïch	travel-ielts-task2-technology-and-travel	In recent years, technology has greatly changed the way people travel and plan their trips. Discuss how technology has affected the travel industry and individuals' travel experiences.	C├┤ng nghß╗ç ─æ├ú thay ─æß╗òi ─æ├íng kß╗â c├ích ch├║ng ta l├¬n kß║┐ hoß║ích v├á trß║úi nghiß╗çm c├íc chuyß║┐n ─æi. H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n vß╗ü nhß╗»ng thay ─æß╗òi n├áy v├á t├íc ─æß╗Öng cß╗ºa ch├║ng.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	5	t	2026-07-14 19:04:44.363	2026-07-14 19:04:44.363	20	\N	0	Technology has indeed transformed travel in many ways. Firstly, booking trips has become much easier. With websites and apps, people can find and book flights, hotels, and tours from home. For example, a few clicks can secure a holiday package. Secondly, navigation is simpler. GPS and mapping apps mean tourists rarely get lost, even in foreign cities. This makes exploring new places less stressful. Thirdly, sharing travel experiences is instant. Travelers can upload photos and videos to social media right away, inspiring others. However, some argue that technology makes travel less authentic, as people are always looking at their phones instead of their surroundings. Overall, technology has made travel more accessible and convenient for most people.
