6004bb75-f9e4-4747-919c-7de7b6363cc6	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Nhß╗»ng phß║⌐m chß║Ñt cß╗ºa mß╗Öt gi├ío vi├¬n giß╗Åi	education-sentence-qualities-good-teacher	H├úy viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân ngß║»n (tß╗½ 80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü nhß╗»ng phß║⌐m chß║Ñt m├á bß║ín ngh─⌐ l├á quan trß╗ìng nhß║Ñt ß╗ƒ mß╗Öt gi├ío vi├¬n giß╗Åi. Mß╗Öt gi├ío vi├¬n giß╗Åi n├¬n c├│ nhß╗»ng ─æß║╖c ─æiß╗âm n├áo ─æß╗â gi├║p hß╗ìc sinh hß╗ìc tß╗æt v├á y├¬u th├¡ch viß╗çc hß╗ìc.	Viß║┐t vß╗ü nhß╗»ng phß║⌐m chß║Ñt quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa mß╗Öt gi├ío vi├¬n giß╗Åi v├á hß╗ì ß║únh h╞░ß╗ƒng ─æß║┐n hß╗ìc sinh nh╞░ thß║┐ n├áo.	80	150	B1	SENTENCE	4	t	2026-07-14 19:05:00.15	2026-07-14 19:05:00.15	20	\N	0	A good teacher has many important qualities. Firstly, they should be patient and understanding with their students. Not everyone learns at the same speed, so patience is key. Secondly, a good teacher must be knowledgeable about their subject and able to explain difficult ideas clearly. They also need to be enthusiastic because their passion for the subject can inspire students. Furthermore, they should be fair and treat all students equally. A teacher who listens to students and encourages them to ask questions helps create a positive learning environment. Good teachers don't just teach lessons; they also teach life skills and make learning enjoyable.
caa24017-b45d-466a-ad60-31ed5201391a	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Mß╗Ñc ti├¬u gi├ío dß╗Ñc v├á sß╗▒ nghiß╗çp t╞░╞íng lai	education-sentence-future-goals	H├úy viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân ngß║»n (tß╗½ 80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü mß╗Ñc ti├¬u gi├ío dß╗Ñc v├á sß╗▒ nghiß╗çp t╞░╞íng lai cß╗ºa bß║ín. Bß║ín muß╗æn hß╗ìc ng├ánh g├¼, l├ám c├┤ng viß╗çc g├¼, v├á tß║íi sao bß║ín chß╗ìn con ─æ╞░ß╗¥ng ─æ├│?	Viß║┐t vß╗ü ╞░ß╗¢c m╞í v├á mß╗Ñc ti├¬u cß╗ºa bß║ín sau khi ho├án th├ánh viß╗çc hß╗ìc.	80	150	B1	SENTENCE	5	t	2026-07-14 19:05:00.154	2026-07-14 19:05:00.154	20	\N	0	After I finish high school, my main goal is to study Information Technology at university. I am very interested in computers and how technology can solve problems. I want to learn about programming, software development, and cybersecurity. I believe this field has a lot of opportunities for the future. My dream job is to become a software engineer and create useful applications that can help people in their daily lives. I also want to contribute to the development of new technologies. I think studying IT will allow me to be creative and always learn new things. I am excited about this path and ready to work hard to achieve my dreams.
9cc40c2e-002f-4f1a-b0cf-1edca34e2bb3	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa viß╗çc hß╗ìc tiß║┐ng Anh	education-paragraph-benefits-of-learning-english	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü nhß╗»ng lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa viß╗çc hß╗ìc tiß║┐ng Anh ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i hß╗ìc sinh, sinh vi├¬n v├á trong cuß╗Öc sß╗æng. H├úy tr├¼nh b├áy ├¡t nhß║Ñt hai lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗Ñ thß╗â.	Viß║┐t vß╗ü nhß╗»ng lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa viß╗çc hß╗ìc tiß║┐ng Anh trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc v├á cuß╗Öc sß╗æng h├áng ng├áy.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	1	t	2026-07-14 19:05:09.619	2026-07-14 19:05:09.619	20	\N	0	Learning English offers many great benefits for students and in daily life. First, it opens doors to more educational opportunities. Many advanced courses and research materials are available in English, helping students expand their knowledge. For example, they can read international books or study abroad. Second, English improves career prospects. In today's global job market, many companies require employees to speak English, especially in fields like tourism, technology, and business. Being fluent in English can lead to better jobs and higher salaries. Furthermore, it helps people communicate with others from different countries, making travel and cultural exchange much easier and more enjoyable. Therefore, learning English is a valuable skill for everyone.
ff3faf8c-0ed9-463d-9332-daae6e8c27ac	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n so vß╗¢i hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng	education-paragraph-online-vs-traditional-learning	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (80-150 tß╗½) so s├ính hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n v├á hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng. H├úy n├¬u mß╗Öt ╞░u ─æiß╗âm cß╗ºa hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n v├á mß╗Öt ╞░u ─æiß╗âm cß╗ºa hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng, c├╣ng vß╗¢i mß╗Öt nh╞░ß╗úc ─æiß╗âm cß╗ºa mß╗ùi h├¼nh thß╗⌐c.	So s├ính ╞░u v├á nh╞░ß╗úc ─æiß╗âm cß╗ºa hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n v├á hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	2	t	2026-07-14 19:05:09.642	2026-07-14 19:05:09.642	20	\N	0	Online learning and traditional classroom learning both have their pros and cons. Online learning offers great flexibility; students can study from anywhere and at their own pace, which is perfect for those with busy schedules. However, a major disadvantage is the lack of face-to-face interaction, which can make it harder to ask questions immediately or collaborate with classmates. On the other hand, traditional learning provides a structured environment and direct interaction with teachers and peers, fostering better communication skills and a sense of community. The main drawback of traditional learning can be its fixed schedule and location, which might not suit everyone's needs. Ultimately, the best choice depends on individual preferences and learning styles.
8051d0ea-fd58-4b0d-9f1e-ffdc839f4b06	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa gi├ío vi├¬n	education-paragraph-importance-of-teachers	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa gi├ío vi├¬n trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc. H├úy giß║úi th├¡ch tß║íi sao gi├ío vi├¬n l├á yß║┐u tß╗æ then chß╗æt cho sß╗▒ th├ánh c├┤ng cß╗ºa hß╗ìc sinh.	Viß║┐t vß╗ü vai tr├▓ v├á tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa gi├ío vi├¬n trong hß╗ç thß╗æng gi├ío dß╗Ñc.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	3	t	2026-07-14 19:05:09.659	2026-07-14 19:05:09.659	20	\N	0	Teachers play a crucial role in the education system and in shaping students' lives. They are not just instructors who deliver knowledge; they are also mentors, guides, and motivators. A good teacher can inspire students to love learning, explore new ideas, and overcome challenges. For example, they can make complex subjects easier to understand and help students develop critical thinking skills. Teachers also provide valuable emotional support and encouragement, helping students build confidence and resilience. Furthermore, they teach important life skills like discipline, teamwork, and problem-solving, which are essential for future success. Without dedicated teachers, even the best curriculum would struggle to achieve its goals, proving their irreplaceable value in every student's journey.
d7f6eefb-ec23-470b-95d9-eecf4a98d873	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	C├┤ng nghß╗ç trong lß╗¢p hß╗ìc hiß╗çn ─æß║íi	education-paragraph-technology-in-classrooms	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü t├íc ─æß╗Öng cß╗ºa c├┤ng nghß╗ç trong lß╗¢p hß╗ìc hiß╗çn ─æß║íi. H├úy n├¬u mß╗Öt lß╗úi ├¡ch v├á mß╗Öt th├ích thß╗⌐c khi sß╗¡ dß╗Ñng c├┤ng nghß╗ç trong gi├ío dß╗Ñc.	Thß║úo luß║¡n vß╗ü t├íc ─æß╗Öng cß╗ºa c├┤ng nghß╗ç ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i viß╗çc hß╗ìc v├á dß║íy trong c├íc lß╗¢p hß╗ìc ng├áy nay.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	4	t	2026-07-14 19:05:09.667	2026-07-14 19:05:09.667	20	\N	0	Technology has brought significant changes to modern classrooms, offering both benefits and challenges. One major benefit is that technology makes learning more engaging and interactive. Tools like interactive whiteboards, educational apps, and online videos can help teachers explain difficult concepts more clearly and make lessons more interesting for students. For instance, students can take virtual field trips or use simulations to understand scientific principles. However, a significant challenge is the potential for distraction. Students might use devices for non-educational purposes during class, such as playing games or checking social media, which can hinder their concentration and learning. Therefore, while technology can be a powerful educational tool, it requires careful management by teachers to maximize its positive impact and minimize its downsides.
