3e6ecf56-7110-4b1b-be8f-89f67f3bd1eb	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	The Role of Homework in Learning	education-essay-role-of-homework	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt b├ái luß║¡n vß╗ü vai tr├▓ cß╗ºa b├ái tß║¡p vß╗ü nh├á trong qu├í tr├¼nh hß╗ìc tß║¡p cß╗ºa hß╗ìc sinh. Bß║ín ngh─⌐ b├ái tß║¡p vß╗ü nh├á c├│ cß║ºn thiß║┐t kh├┤ng v├á tß║íi sao?	Discuss the importance of homework for students' learning process.	80	150	B1	ESSAY	1	t	2026-07-14 19:05:25.59	2026-07-14 19:05:25.59	20	\N	0	Homework is an important part of learning for students. It helps students practice what they learned in class. When students do homework, they review the lessons and remember information better. Also, homework teaches students to be responsible and manage their time. For example, if a student has math homework and English homework, they must plan how to finish both. This skill is useful for their future. Some people think homework is too much, but I believe a reasonable amount helps students succeed. It reinforces learning and builds good study habits.
