3b9ab9f1-e847-4949-bf47-d22b7b839ce4	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	The Benefits of Extracurricular Activities	education-essay-benefits-extracurricular	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt b├ái luß║¡n vß╗ü lß╗úi ├¡ch cß╗ºa c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng ngoß║íi kh├│a (v├¡ dß╗Ñ: c├óu lß║íc bß╗Ö, thß╗â thao, ├óm nhß║íc) ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i hß╗ìc sinh.	Explain why extracurricular activities are important for students' overall development.	80	150	B1	ESSAY	5	t	2026-07-14 19:05:25.627	2026-07-14 19:05:25.627	20	\N	0	Extracurricular activities are very important for students, not just studying. These activities include sports, music clubs, art classes, or volunteer work. They help students develop new skills that they don't learn in regular lessons. For example, playing in a team sport teaches teamwork and leadership. Learning a musical instrument improves discipline and creativity. Also, these activities help students relieve stress from schoolwork and make new friends with similar interests. They can also discover new passions and build confidence. Therefore, schools should encourage students to join extracurricular activities because they help students grow into well-rounded individuals.
