715fe10e-7fff-45b7-97ce-79a4c0cdbae5	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Student Participation in Extracurricular Activities (2010 & 2020)	education-ielts-task1-student-extracurricular-activities	The table below presents the number of students participating in three types of extracurricular activities (Sports Clubs, Academic Clubs, and Volunteering) at a high school in 2010 and 2020. In 2010, Sports Clubs had 150, Academic Clubs 80, and Volunteering 60. In 2020, Sports Clubs had 180, Academic Clubs 120, and Volunteering 100. Summarize the information by selecting and reporting the main features, and make comparisons where relevant.	Hß╗ìc vi├¬n sß║╜ m├┤ tß║ú mß╗Öt bß║úng sß╗æ liß╗çu so s├ính sß╗æ l╞░ß╗úng hß╗ìc sinh tham gia c├íc hoß║ít ─æß╗Öng ngoß║íi kh├│a kh├íc nhau tß║íi mß╗Öt tr╞░ß╗¥ng hß╗ìc trong hai n─âm.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_1	4	t	2026-07-14 19:06:40.856	2026-07-14 19:06:40.856	20	\N	0	The table shows student participation in three extracurricular activities at a high school in 2010 and 2020. Overall, the number of students joining all three types of activities increased over the decade, with Sports Clubs remaining the most popular.\n\nIn 2010, Sports Clubs had the highest number of participants with 150 students. Academic Clubs attracted 80 students, and Volunteering had the fewest, with 60 participants. By 2020, all activities saw growth. Sports Clubs increased to 180 students. Academic Clubs experienced a significant rise to 120 students. Volunteering also became more popular, with 100 students participating. This indicates a general increase in student engagement in extracurricular activities over the ten-year period.
686c33a5-3fb9-4050-9877-935da8d45c71	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Parental Choice of School Types in UK and Vietnam (2023)	education-ielts-task1-parental-school-choice-uk-vietnam	The two pie charts below compare the proportion of parents choosing different types of schools (Public Schools, Private Schools, and Home Schooling) for their children in the UK and Vietnam in 2023. In the UK, Public Schools were 70%, Private Schools 20%, Home Schooling 10%. In Vietnam, Public Schools were 85%, Private Schools 10%, Home Schooling 5%. Summarize the information by selecting and reporting the main features, and make comparisons where relevant.	Hß╗ìc vi├¬n sß║╜ m├┤ tß║ú hai biß╗âu ─æß╗ô tr├▓n so s├ính tß╗╖ lß╗ç phß╗Ñ huynh lß╗▒a chß╗ìn c├íc loß║íi h├¼nh tr╞░ß╗¥ng hß╗ìc kh├íc nhau (c├┤ng lß║¡p, t╞░ thß╗Ñc, tß║íi nh├á) cho con c├íi cß╗ºa hß╗ì ß╗ƒ hai quß╗æc gia kh├íc nhau.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_1	5	t	2026-07-14 19:06:40.861	2026-07-14 19:06:40.861	20	\N	0	The two pie charts illustrate the types of schools parents chose for their children in the UK and Vietnam in 2023. Overall, public schools were the most popular choice in both countries, but their share was much higher in Vietnam.\n\nIn the UK, public schools accounted for 70% of parental choices. Private schools were chosen by 20% of parents, while home schooling made up 10%. In contrast, Vietnam showed an even stronger preference for public education, with 85% of parents choosing public schools. Private schools were less popular, at 10%, and home schooling was the least common option, at only 5%. This indicates that while public education is dominant in both nations, it plays an even larger role in Vietnam.
44dae1eb-fe6e-4996-9064-522a813b519e	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Online Learning vs. Traditional Classroom	education-ielts-task-2-online-vs-traditional-learning	Ng├áy nay, nhiß╗üu hß╗ìc sinh v├á sinh vi├¬n lß╗▒a chß╗ìn hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n, trong khi nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc vß║½n th├¡ch m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng lß╗¢p hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng. H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n vß╗ü nhß╗»ng ╞░u ─æiß╗âm v├á nh╞░ß╗úc ─æiß╗âm cß╗ºa viß╗çc hß╗ìc trß╗▒c tuyß║┐n c┼⌐ng nh╞░ gi├ío dß╗Ñc trong lß╗¢p hß╗ìc truyß╗ün thß╗æng. Theo bß║ín, ph╞░╞íng ph├íp n├áo hiß╗çu quß║ú h╞ín cho ─æa sß╗æ hß╗ìc sinh, v├á tß║íi sao?	Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of studying online compared to traditional classroom settings. Which method do you think is more effective for most students?	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	1	t	2026-07-16 19:00:17.768	2026-07-16 19:00:17.768	20	\N	0	Both online learning and traditional classrooms have good points and bad points. Online learning is very flexible, allowing students to study anywhere and anytime. This is great for people who work or have other commitments. However, online students might miss face-to-face interaction and real-time discussions with classmates and teachers. Traditional classrooms offer a lively environment where students can ask questions immediately and learn from group work. But they can be less flexible with schedules and location. I think traditional classrooms are usually more effective for most students, especially younger ones, because they provide a structured environment and help develop important social skills.
f4338ebd-67db-4777-84c7-827f5d44b2fd	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	University Degrees vs. Vocational Skills	education-ielts-task-2-university-vs-vocational-skills	Mß╗Öt sß╗æ ng╞░ß╗¥i tin rß║▒ng viß╗çc c├│ bß║▒ng ─æß║íi hß╗ìc l├á ─æiß╗üu cß║ºn thiß║┐t ─æß╗â c├│ mß╗Öt sß╗▒ nghiß╗çp tß╗æt, trong khi nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi cho rß║▒ng c├íc kß╗╣ n─âng thß╗▒c tß║┐ v├á ─æ├áo tß║ío nghß╗ü mß╗¢i quan trß╗ìng h╞ín. H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n cß║ú hai quan ─æiß╗âm n├áy v├á ─æ╞░a ra ├╜ kiß║┐n cß╗ºa ri├¬ng bß║ín.	Explore the debate between pursuing a university degree and acquiring practical vocational skills for future careers. Which path is more valuable?	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	2	t	2026-07-16 19:00:17.8	2026-07-16 19:00:17.8	20	\N	0	Some people think a university degree is the best way to get a good job, while others prefer practical skills. A university degree often teaches critical thinking and broad knowledge, which can be useful for many careers. However, it can be expensive and take a long time. Vocational training, on the other hand, teaches specific skills needed for a particular job, like mechanics or cooking. This can lead to employment faster and often costs less. I believe both paths are valuable, but practical skills are becoming more important today because they directly prepare people for specific roles in the job market, which is often what employers need.
60c78baa-6536-4da7-a0cc-4d08e83b0252	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	The Role of Technology in Modern Education	education-ielts-task-2-technology-in-education	Trong nhß╗»ng n─âm gß║ºn ─æ├óy, c├┤ng nghß╗ç ─æ├ú trß╗ƒ th├ánh mß╗Öt phß║ºn quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa gi├ío dß╗Ñc. Nhß╗»ng lß╗úi ├¡ch v├á hß║ín chß║┐ ch├¡nh cß╗ºa viß╗çc sß╗¡ dß╗Ñng c├┤ng nghß╗ç trong lß╗¢p hß╗ìc l├á g├¼? Bß║ín c├│ ngh─⌐ rß║▒ng c├┤ng nghß╗ç gi├║p hß╗ìc sinh hß╗ìc tß║¡p hiß╗çu quß║ú h╞ín kh├┤ng?	Analyze the main benefits and drawbacks of using technology in classrooms. Does technology help students learn more effectively?	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	3	t	2026-07-16 19:00:17.81	2026-07-16 19:00:17.81	20	\N	0	Technology has changed how we learn in schools. A main benefit is that students can access a lot of information easily from the internet. Interactive tools and apps also make lessons more fun and engaging. However, there are drawbacks too. Students might get distracted by social media or games, and too much screen time can be bad for their eyes. Also, not all students have access to technology at home, which can create inequality. Overall, I think technology can help students learn more effectively, but teachers must use it wisely and balance it with traditional teaching methods to get the best results.
2ebc932b-089c-4b46-b3a3-beb2cbdbc8c7	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	The Importance of Lifelong Learning	education-ielts-task-2-lifelong-learning	Gi├ío dß╗Ñc th╞░ß╗¥ng ─æ╞░ß╗úc xem l├á qu├í tr├¼nh diß╗àn ra chß╗º yß║┐u ß╗ƒ tr╞░ß╗¥ng hß╗ìc v├á ─æß║íi hß╗ìc. Tuy nhi├¬n, nhiß╗üu ng╞░ß╗¥i tin rß║▒ng viß╗çc hß╗ìc n├¬n tiß║┐p tß╗Ñc trong suß╗æt cuß╗Öc ─æß╗¥i cß╗ºa mß╗Öt ng╞░ß╗¥i. Tß║íi sao bß║ín ngh─⌐ hß╗ìc tß║¡p suß╗æt ─æß╗¥i lß║íi quan trß╗ìng, v├á ─æ├óu l├á mß╗Öt sß╗æ c├ích m├á mß╗ìi ng╞░ß╗¥i c├│ thß╗â tiß║┐p tß╗Ñc hß╗ìc sau khi kß║┐t th├║c gi├ío dß╗Ñc ch├¡nh quy?	Discuss why people should continue learning throughout their lives, not just during formal schooling, and suggest ways to do so.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	4	t	2026-07-16 19:00:17.819	2026-07-16 19:00:17.819	20	\N	0	Many people agree that learning should not stop after school or university; it should continue throughout life. Lifelong learning is important for several reasons. First, the world is changing fast, so new skills are always needed for jobs. Second, it helps people grow personally and stay curious about new things. Third, it keeps the brain active and healthy. People can continue to learn in many ways, such as reading books, taking online courses, joining workshops, or even learning new hobbies. These activities help us adapt to new situations and improve ourselves constantly in a changing world.
4bfe5959-69cf-4d68-bd03-17239e87b121	bf13dc19-fde0-4940-89f4-205214ee9268	Discipline in Schools: Too Strict or Too Lenient?	education-ielts-task-2-discipline-in-schools	Mß╗Öt sß╗æ ng╞░ß╗¥i cho rß║▒ng kß╗╖ luß║¡t ß╗ƒ tr╞░ß╗¥ng hß╗ìc ng├áy nay qu├í lß╗Ång lß║╗o, dß║½n ─æß║┐n h├ánh vi sai tr├íi, trong khi nhß╗»ng ng╞░ß╗¥i kh├íc lß║íi tin rß║▒ng kß╗╖ luß║¡t qu├í nghi├¬m khß║»c c├│ thß╗â l├ám tß╗òn hß║íi ─æß║┐n sß╗▒ s├íng tß║ío v├á hß║ính ph├║c cß╗ºa hß╗ìc sinh. H├úy thß║úo luß║¡n cß║ú hai quan ─æiß╗âm v├á n├¬u ├╜ kiß║┐n cß╗ºa ri├¬ng bß║ín vß╗ü c├ích c├íc tr╞░ß╗¥ng hß╗ìc n├¬n tiß║┐p cß║¡n kß╗╖ luß║¡t hß╗ìc sinh.	Examine the current state of discipline in schools and whether it is appropriate. Discuss both perspectives and state your own view.	80	150	B1	IELTS_TASK_2	5	t	2026-07-16 19:00:17.827	2026-07-16 19:00:17.827	20	\N	0	The topic of discipline in schools is often debated. Some argue that schools are too lenient, leading to students not respecting rules. This can make learning difficult for everyone and affect the overall environment. Others believe that being too strict can stop students from being creative and make them feel scared, which is not good for their well-being and confidence. In my opinion, schools need a good balance. There should be clear rules and consequences for bad behavior, but also a supportive environment where students feel safe to express themselves and learn from their mistakes. Discipline should teach responsibility, not just punish.
5ba89571-9320-4972-a80c-42cac4dc57bc	a9107456-5182-4e8e-bf13-0adc4946b8fb	My Daily Healthy Habits	health-sentence-my-daily-healthy-habits	H├úy m├┤ tß║ú nhß╗»ng th├│i quen l├ánh mß║ính h├áng ng├áy cß╗ºa bß║ín. Bß║ín l├ám g├¼ mß╗ùi ng├áy ─æß╗â giß╗» g├¼n sß╗⌐c khß╗Åe? V├¡ dß╗Ñ: ─ân s├íng, tß║¡p thß╗â dß╗Ñc, ngß╗º sß╗¢m.	Write about the simple things you do every day to stay healthy.	80	150	B1	SENTENCE	1	t	2026-07-16 19:00:58.84	2026-07-16 19:00:58.84	20	\N	0	Staying healthy is important for a good life. Every morning, I try to wake up early, around 6:30 AM. First, I drink a glass of water, which helps my body start fresh. For breakfast, I usually eat oatmeal with some fruit, like a banana or apples. This gives me energy for the day. Before going to work, I often take a short walk for about 20 minutes. It makes me feel active. During lunch, I always choose healthy options, like a salad or a meal with lots of vegetables. In the evening, I cook dinner at home and try to finish eating before 7 PM. Finally, I make sure to go to bed by 10 PM to get enough sleep. These small habits help me feel good and healthy every day.
3c31b157-1a30-4ba5-af77-a559ea45d276	a9107456-5182-4e8e-bf13-0adc4946b8fb	The Power of Exercise	health-sentence-the-power-of-exercise	H├úy giß║úi th├¡ch tß║íi sao tß║¡p thß╗â dß╗Ñc lß║íi quan trß╗ìng ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i sß╗⌐c khß╗Åe cß╗ºa ch├║ng ta. Bß║ín th├¡ch nhß╗»ng loß║íi h├¼nh tß║¡p luyß╗çn n├áo v├á ch├║ng gi├║p ├¡ch g├¼ cho c╞í thß╗â v├á tinh thß║ºn cß╗ºa bß║ín?	Explain why physical exercise is important and mention your favorite activities.	80	150	B1	SENTENCE	2	t	2026-07-16 19:00:58.848	2026-07-16 19:00:58.848	20	\N	0	Exercise is very important for our health. It helps our body stay strong and makes us feel happier. When we exercise, our heart becomes stronger, and our muscles get bigger. This can prevent many diseases. Also, exercise is good for our mind. It helps reduce stress and makes us sleep better at night. I enjoy walking in the park with my friends. It is a simple exercise, but it makes me feel refreshed and happy. Sometimes, I also go swimming. Swimming is a full-body workout, and it is very relaxing. After swimming, I always feel calm and energized. Doing these activities regularly keeps me healthy both physically and mentally.
