17228f17-07e7-4cf1-98b2-c28803ee68c9	5a5f69d1-b29d-48ad-bac3-e0898fc7820b	Tackling Air Pollution	environment-paragraph-tackling-air-pollution	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (khoß║úng 80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü ├┤ nhiß╗àm kh├┤ng kh├¡. Bß║ín h├úy n├¬u ra mß╗Öt sß╗æ nguy├¬n nh├ón ch├¡nh g├óy ├┤ nhiß╗àm kh├┤ng kh├¡ v├á ─æß╗ü xuß║Ñt mß╗Öt v├ái c├ích ─æ╞ín giß║ún m├á ch├║ng ta c├│ thß╗â l├ám ─æß╗â giß║úm thiß╗âu n├│ trong cuß╗Öc sß╗æng h├áng ng├áy.	Explain the main causes of air pollution and suggest simple ways to reduce it.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	2	t	2026-07-16 19:02:26.924	2026-07-16 19:02:26.924	20	\N	0	Air pollution is a serious problem that affects our health and the environment. One main cause is exhaust fumes from cars and motorbikes, especially in big cities. Factories also release harmful gases into the air. Burning rubbish or fossil fuels for energy adds to the pollution too. This bad air can cause breathing problems for people and damage plants. To reduce air pollution, we can try to walk or cycle more often instead of driving. Using public transport is another good option. We should also avoid burning trash and support clean energy sources like solar power. Even small changes in our daily habits can make a difference in making the air cleaner for everyone.
4b08bf8b-41ff-4666-a27f-eaca6ad4eedc	5a5f69d1-b29d-48ad-bac3-e0898fc7820b	Saving Water at Home	environment-paragraph-saving-water-at-home	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (khoß║úng 80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü tß║ºm quan trß╗ìng cß╗ºa viß╗çc tiß║┐t kiß╗çm n╞░ß╗¢c. Bß║ín c├│ thß╗â giß║úi th├¡ch tß║íi sao n╞░ß╗¢c sß║ích lß║íi qu├╜ gi├í v├á ─æ╞░a ra mß╗Öt sß╗æ mß║╣o ─æ╞ín giß║ún ─æß╗â tiß║┐t kiß╗çm n╞░ß╗¢c trong nh├á bß║ín hoß║╖c ß╗ƒ tr╞░ß╗¥ng.	Discuss why water conservation is crucial and provide practical tips for saving water in everyday life.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	3	t	2026-07-16 19:02:26.934	2026-07-16 19:02:26.934	20	\N	0	Water is a precious resource, and saving it is very important for everyone. Although water covers most of the Earth, only a small amount is fresh water that we can drink or use for farming. Many places around the world suffer from water shortages, so we must be careful with how we use it. We can save water easily at home. For example, turn off the tap when you brush your teeth or wash dishes. Taking shorter showers instead of long baths also helps a lot. We should also check for leaky pipes and fix them quickly because even small leaks waste a lot of water. By being mindful of our water usage, we can help ensure there is enough for future generations.
8fc36525-d2dd-4457-ac02-eed5d4fa308b	5a5f69d1-b29d-48ad-bac3-e0898fc7820b	The Impact of Deforestation	environment-paragraph-impact-of-deforestation	Viß║┐t mß╗Öt ─æoß║ín v─ân (khoß║úng 80-150 tß╗½) vß╗ü nß║ín ph├í rß╗½ng (deforestation). Bß║ín h├úy giß║úi th├¡ch nguy├¬n nh├ón g├óy ra ph├í rß╗½ng v├á t├íc ─æß╗Öng ti├¬u cß╗▒c cß╗ºa n├│ ─æß╗æi vß╗¢i m├┤i tr╞░ß╗¥ng. Sau ─æ├│, ─æß╗ü xuß║Ñt mß╗Öt v├ái c├ích ch├║ng ta c├│ thß╗â gi├║p bß║úo vß╗ç rß╗½ng.	Explore the causes and negative effects of deforestation, and suggest ways to combat it.	80	150	B1	PARAGRAPH	4	t	2026-07-16 19:02:26.941	2026-07-16 19:02:26.941	20	\N	0	Deforestation, which is the clearing of forests, is a big problem for our planet. People cut down trees mainly for farming, logging to get wood, and building new towns or roads. When forests are destroyed, many animals lose their homes, and some even become endangered. Trees are also very important because they produce oxygen for us to breathe and absorb carbon dioxide, a gas that contributes to climate change. Without trees, the soil can become dry and lead to floods or mudslides. To help combat deforestation, we can plant more trees and choose products made from recycled paper. Supporting organizations that protect forests is also a good way to make a difference.
